        {
          "obj_id": "thm:sharp-pointwise-lower-bound",
          "kind": "theorem",
          "label": "Theorem T-1",
          "nl": "Assume ass:baseline-submodel-slack. Then for every beta>0 there exists a constant c > 0, depending only on the fixed model radii and the slack baseline, such that for all sufficiently large n, R_n(P_{alpha,beta,s}(M,c_0,epsilon_0,t_0), t_0) >= c n^(-2*alpha/(2*alpha+1)). Equivalently, uniformly over every beta>0, every estimator of theta_P(t_0) over P_{alpha,beta,s}(M,c_0,epsilon_0,t_0) has worst-case mean-squared error at least a constant multiple of the classical interior treatment-regression pointwise rate.",
